# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  RMOOZ offline Docker — build context exclusions
#  Build context: UI_MOdified/ (the project root)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Git and IDE ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore
.claude
*.claude/

# ── Node.js ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# node_modules will be rebuilt inside the container via npm install
node_modules
npm-*.log
*.log
# `*.log` is NOT recursive in Docker ignore (a `*` never crosses `/`), so nested
# logs like server/logs/web-server.err.log slipped through and baked Windows dev
# paths into the image. Catch logs recursively + exclude EVERY runtime log dir at
# any depth (incl. the offline overlay's server tree). These never belong in the image.
**/*.log
**/*.log.*
logs/
server/logs
server/logs/
offline_app/server/logs/
Offline_Deployment/offline_app/server/logs/
**/logs
**/logs/
# Runtime state pointers that record absolute host paths (scenario watcher writes
# the active-scenario pointer with a machine path). Pure runtime — never baked.
_active.json
**/_active.json

# ── Python caches ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo

# ── TestingAI exclusions ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Windows .venv — NOT compatible with Linux container; container gets its own
# Python venv at /opt/rmooz-venv built from requirements.offline.txt
TestingAI/.venv

# SmartSearch is 2.2 GB (torch, transformers, fastembed models, Qdrant data).
# Excluded to keep image size manageable. WarGamingGEN uses Markdown fallback
# for doctrine retrieval when SmartSearch is absent.
TestingAI/SmartSearch

# Runtime I/O directories — mounted as volumes at compose time
TestingAI/export_to_rmooz
TestingAI/import_from_rmooz
TestingAI/WarGamingGEN/runs

# Stale dev artifact: WarGamingGEN/.env carries a Windows dev path + localhost
# Ollama creds. MUST NEVER bake into the image. config.py only load_dotenv()s it
# when present, and the bridge injects LLM_* at spawn time, so excluding it is safe
# (the offline LiteLLM env comes from .env.offline → buildLlmChildEnv).
TestingAI/WarGamingGEN/.env
TestingAI/WarGamingGEN/.env.*
TestingAI/WarGamingGEN/runs/
**/.env
**/.env.*

# TestingAI top-level dev notes / screenshots are NOT runtime artifacts (the
# WarGamingGEN Python pipeline imports none of them). SESSION_WARGAMINGGEN_REVIEW_
# HANDOFF.md also carries an absolute C:\Users dev path — must never bake.
TestingAI/*.md
TestingAI/*.png
TestingAI/.__archive
# macOS AppleDouble resource-fork droppings (committed from a Mac) — pure junk.
**/._*

# Large, OPTIONAL, gitignored GIS data (DEM raster + terrain/imagery layers, ~960 MB).
# NOT part of origin/main; gis_loader treats elevation/terrain as optional and
# degrades gracefully when absent. Excluded so the image reflects committed source
# and stays lean. If terrain-aware generation is wanted, mount inputs/gis at runtime.
TestingAI/WarGamingGEN/inputs/gis

# Step 0 planning artifacts — not needed at runtime
TestingAI/Step 0
TestingAI/_archive

# ── Runtime data (mounted as volumes) ─────────────────────────────────────────
data
uploads
maps

# ── Offline_Deployment runtime directories (not needed in image) ──────────────
Offline_Deployment/map_data/base
Offline_Deployment/map_data/terrain
Offline_Deployment/map_data/styles
Offline_Deployment/map_data/attribution
Offline_Deployment/TestingAI_Runtime
Offline_Deployment/.env.offline

# ── Docs and tests (not needed in runtime image) ─────────────────────────────
docs
test-*.js
**/test-*.js
scripts/test-*.js
*.test.js

# ── Build output / transfer bundle (never belongs in the image context) ──────
Offline_Deployment/dist

# ── Development artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DOC-UNDERSTANDING-1: devtools verify harnesses / fixtures are never runtime.
devtools
**/devtools
*.bat
*.tar.gz
*.tar
web-server.log
web-server.err.log
.runtime-logs/
